definition: between/among/within a definite time or space/room/section of a room or lateral space between two pairs of pillars/classifier for rooms
gap/to separate/to thin out (seedlings)/to sow discontent

sentences.english: An intense ring of stars forms at the outer edges of the new, combined galaxy.
sentences.chinese: 激烈的環星形式在外層空間邊緣，新合併的星系。

sentences.english: IT was 37 seconds long and came from outer space.
sentences.chinese: 這個信號長達37秒，而且是來自外層空間。

sentences.english: The two space vehicles docked in space and exchanged astronauts.
sentences.chinese: 兩個宇宙飛行器在外層空間對接並交換宇航員。

sentences.english: The scientists are still working on inventing new methods of reaching outer space.
sentences.chinese: 科學家們仍致力於發明到達外層空間的新方法。

sentences.english: The project heralds a shift in the balance of power among spacefaring nations.
sentences.chinese: 這個計劃預示着國家外層空間力量的平衡將被打破。
